As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 405 people, 174 households, and 117 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Jupiter+Inlet+Colony+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|access-date=June 30, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 400 people, 198 households, and 135 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Jupiter+Inlet+Colony+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|access-date=September 24, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

===2000 census===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]] there were 368 people, 180 households, and 124 families in the town.  The population density was {{convert|2,090.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 229 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,300.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census#2000 census|racial makeup]] of the town was 99.73% White, and 0.27% from other races. Of the 180 households 12.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 64.4% were married couples living together, 3.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.1% were non-families. 23.9% of households were one person and 15.0% were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.04 and the average family size was 2.38.

In 2000, the age distribution was 10.6% under the age of 18, 1.1% from 18 to 24, 12.2% from 25 to 44, 36.1% from 45 to 64, and 39.9% 65 or older. The median age was 60 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.4 males.

In 2000, the median household income was $65,938 and the median family income  was $93,554. Males had a median income of $90,000 versus $41,875 for females. The per capita income for the town was $66,713. About 1.6% of families and 3.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 10.0% of those under age 18 and 1.2% of those age 65 or over.

As of 2000, 100% of the population spoke [[English language|English]] as their [[first language]]. It, along with [[Briny Breezes, Florida|Briny Breezes]], [[Cloud Lake, Florida|Cloud Lake]], and [[Golf, Florida|Golf]], were the only [[municipality|municipalities]] in Palm Beach county with all residents having the [[mother tongue]] of English.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=place&zip=&place_id=35900&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA Data Center Results of Jupiter Colony Inlet, FL |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |access-date=November 12, 2007}}</ref>

